The PhD studies will be performed in written form according to demands of University of Tartu. The PhD studies and disputation will be declared officially successful after the scientific council of the Institute of Computer Science has delivered positive judgement and attested it.Objectives/eesmärkid:  PhD students' research aims to acquire the skills and technical competence necessary for planning and conducting research and present his/her results of study. Research must lead to completion of independent study proposing an original solution to a substantial problem in a particular research field, which presupposes the publication of at least three research papers in leading international journals.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  PhD student who had succesfully completed the course: -has deep knowledge in his/her field of study, is well informed about new developments of research -is capable to identify and formulate research problems -is capable to design and initiate research projects that will lead to new knowledges and solutions -is able to analyse and synthesize information found in the process of reasearch and known before -is able to evaluate results of his/her research in broader background -is able to perform the study results into the form of internationally accepted publication -is well informed about the process of publishing scientific articles in international pre-reviewed journals -is able to evaluate and analyse his/her study results -is able to take ethical position and understands the responsibility in creating and using the results of research -is able to estimate the impact of scientific achievements in the broader background of society -is able to make independently strategic desicions -is able to work in international scientific team -is able to present and argue for his/her scientific results in international scientific events -has good communication, management and public speaking skills.
